    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for go-fdo-server.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 10.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "This package provides a server-side implementation of the FIDO Device Onboard (FDO) specification, written in Go. FDO is an open standard for the late binding of device credentials, allowing for automated and secure on-boarding of devices when they are first powered on in their final location.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* github.com/jackc/pgx/v5: github.com/jackc/pgx: Memory-safety vulnerability (CVE-2026-33816)\n\n* crypto/tls: golang: Go crypto/tls: Denial of Service via multiple TLS 1.3 key update messages (CVE-2026-32283)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
